citation: Proclamation under the Primary Produce Safety Act 2011 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Primary Produce Safety Act 2011

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Primary Produce Safety Act 2011 fix 13 February 2014 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, except for the following provisions, commence:

        (a) sections 31 , 87 , 89 , 90 , 91 , 92 , 93 , 94 and 95 ;
        (b) Schedules 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 , 7 and 8 .
3 February 2014

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

BRYAN GREEN

Minister for Primary Industries and Water

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 12 February 2014

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Primary Industries, Parks, Water and Environment.
